Forts.: 26th April 1843.
                                                                          $.#$
Revd. Mr. Gunder, Tellicherry

                                                 Tellicherry 26th. April 1843.
To Reverend Mr Gundert
Reverend Sir,

In reply to your letter I beg to say, that the 2 bask' s of Claret landed here
from Mlie not having paid the value of import Certificate, and as one of them
you require to send now to Mangalore, you will be under the necessity to pay
half a Rupee the value of stamp paper and Rupee for another Re-export stamp
papper. As then is a boat to sail to that station, I hope you will send the
3/4 Rupee, and avail this oppertunity to send the above Cask. to Mangalore.
.fo -                    I remain to be
                           Reverend Sir
                           your most obedient servant



Rev. S. Hebich, Cannanur, with 1 book

